To perform a check in Java if a file contains only null characters, you can read the file in chunks of bytes and verify if all the bytes in each chunk are zero. Here is how you might go about it using a `BufferedInputStream`:

```java
import java.io.BufferedInputStream;
import java.io.FileInputStream;
import java.io.IOException;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
