Acutuator&#39;s `/actuator/caches` endpoint only shows the configured caches. For cache metrics you should use the following ones:

`/actuator/metrics/cache.gets`  
`/actuator/metrics/cache.puts`  
`/actuator/metrics/cache.evictions`  
`/actuator/metrics/cache.removals`  

Hitting those will show the corresponding metrics for all available caches. If you need to target a specific cache, say `cache1`, you can do it like so:

`/actuator/metrics/cache.gets?tag=name:cache1`

Make sure to expose the `metrics` endpoint by adding it to the `management.endpoints.web.exposure.include` app property, i.e.:

`management.endpoints.web.exposure.include=caches,metrics`

You might need these properties as well: 
```
management.endpoint.metrics.enabled=true
management.endpoint.caches.enabled=true
```

