How do I sort two different arrays in ascending/descending order in a way where I do not use extra space by using an array/collection? The arrays must be sorted considering the elements in both the arrays.

Consider the example below.

Input:

    arr1 = {3,1,8,10,9,7};
    arr2 = {6,4,5,2};

Output:

    arr1 = [1,2,3,4,5,6]
    arr2 = [7,8,9,10]

Point to note:
- Cannot use extra space (not to create a third array or collection).
- Array size cannot change (arr1 must be 6 sized &amp; arr2 must be 4 sized).

I added all the elements in both the arrays into a List named &#39;list&#39; as is (unsorted) and then sorted the list in ascending using streams.

```
list = list.stream()
           .sorted((n1, n2) -&gt; n1-n2)
           .collect(Collectors.toList());
```

Then added the elements in the list back to the array based on their size using below piece of code.

```
for(int i=0; i&lt;arr1.length; i++) {
    arr1[i] = list.get(i);
}
for(int i=0; i&lt;arr2.length; i++) {
    arr2[i] = list.get(i + arr1.length);
}
```

